&lt;p&gt;Liverpool University Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PHARMACY DEPARTMENT&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Pharmacist Aseptic / Clinical Services&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Aseptic Production Unit (Royal Liverpool / Aintree Sites)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 7 + EDC Full time (37.5 hours per week)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a major acute teaching Trust offering a wide range of clinical specialities, including tertiary referrals for HIV and Renal Medicine. Pharmacy services are well developed and deliver high quality Medicines Management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a highly regarded Aseptic Production Unit (APU) at the Trust and a brand new site is due to open in 2021. You will work closely with our Senior Aseptic Services Team to help steer the processes at the production unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post generates an opportunity for an experienced and forward thinking Pharmacist to join a team that is being further developed to cater for the growing pharmaceutical needs of the Trust. The post holder will be expected to focus on the expanding need for Aseptic Services with responsibilities for efficient service provision. You may also have the opportunity to further develop your individual clinical skills to facilitate our ward based clinical pharmacy service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support for appropriate continuing professional development, further technical development such as the PTQA course, is available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
